  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "3364750c-f3ba-8053-a43d-fabefae92924",
      "heading": "Abstract",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Knowledge-based LLM-supported literature recommender; framework also discusses expert-based, multi-criteria, profile-based, and hybrid options, but only knowledge-based is implemented",
          "Literature references and feedback for term paper topic / research question development",
          "~70 students in prior supervision analysis; 56 term paper examples in pilot evaluation",
          "Bachelor of Arts program in Culture and Social Sciences; term-paper supervision context rather than course recommendation",
          "Term Paper Proposal",
          "Topic extraction and categorization from student proposal using LLMs; sentiment analysis used to help trigger recommendation mode; literature selected from static corpus with star-based sorting over concept/reference links",
          "Recommendations generated from each submitted proposal; iterative supervision use case, but no clear automated online updating / retraining reported",
          "Moderation check; LLM extracts top-k topics with explanations and assigned categories; topic filtering via in-context learning; retrieval from concept-linked external resource corpus; final natural-language feedback generated by LLM",
          "Literature recommendations + personalized natural-language feedback / explanations",
          "Expert evaluation with 2 raters on 56 examples using relevance, citation accuracy, citation consistency, usefulness; Cohen’s kappa: relevance 0.5105, accuracy 0.4746, consistency 0.3805, usefulness 0.4683",
          "Interesting because it shifts recommendation from course/resource consumption to academic idea development. Emphasis is on inspiring students, supporting topic refinement, and reducing teacher workload rather than automating writing. Current implementation is only the knowledge-based engine, despite the broader conceptual framework.",
          "Open-ended recommendation setting; no uniform item corpus; small dataset; only pilot expert evaluation; current “star” matching is semantically limited; repeated recommendations / possible popularity bias; creativity evaluation remains unresolved"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
